{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSExpression","text":"NSExpression","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" * "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"textVariableAnchorOffset"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The length of the array must be even, and must alternate between enum and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"point entries. i.e., each anchor location must be accompanied by a point, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that point defines the offset when the corresponding anchor location is used."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Positive offset values indicate right and down, while negative values indicate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"left and up. Anchor locations may repeat, allowing the renderer to try multiple"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"offsets to try and place a label using the same anchor.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When present, this property takes precedence over "},{"code":"textAnchor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"textVariableAnchor"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"textOffset"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"code":"textRadialOffset","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"code":["{ \"text-variable-anchor-offset\": [\"top\", [0, 4], \"left\", [3,0], \"bottom\", [1,","1]] } "],"syntax":"json","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the renderer chooses the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"top"},{"text":" anchor, ","type":"text"},{"code":"[0, 4]","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be used for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"textOffset","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; the text will be shifted down by 4 ems.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When the renderer chooses the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"left"},{"text":" anchor, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[3, 0]"},{"type":"text","text":" will be used for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"textOffset"},{"type":"text","text":"; the text will be shifted right by 3 ems."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This property is only applied to the style if ","type":"text"},{"code":"text","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is non-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"symbolPlacement","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is set to an expression that evaluates to or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNSymbolPlacementPoint"},{"type":"text","text":". Otherwise, it is ignored."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can set this property to an expression containing any of the following:","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Constant interleaved "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNTextAnchor"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CGVector"},{"type":"text","text":" array values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Predefined functions, including mathematical and string operators","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Conditional expressions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Variable assignments and references to assigned variables"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Interpolation and step functions applied to the "},{"code":"$zoomLevel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" variable and\/or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"feature attributes","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer\/textVariableAnchorOffset","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"textVariableAnchorOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNSymbolStyleLayer(py)textVariableAnchorOffset","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"title":"textVariableAnchorOffset","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"textVariableAnchorOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer"]]},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnsymbolstylelayer\/textvariableanchoroffset"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"To increase the chance of placing high-priority labels on the map, you can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"provide an array of "},{"code":"textAnchor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" locations, each paired with an offset value."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The renderer will attempt to place the label at each location, in order, before","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"moving on to the next location+offset. Use "},{"code":"textJustify: auto","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to choose"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"justification based on anchor position."}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","title":"MapLibre","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit w